Introduction¶

In this dataset we will go through medical appointments in Brazil, apparently this dataset provides the detaials of each patient medical wise and have they showed up for the hospital schedualled appointment or not. Besides does they have a medical insurence or financially dependant. some of the questions that maybe asked what factors affect the patient to show up on time for the appointment, what gender is more prone to be committed for the appointment time,have the location of the hospital affect their appearance on the appointment.

Possible Questions¶

Q1: Does the sms being sent to the patient affect their appearance?!

Q2: What gender is more prone to show up for the appointment?

Q3: What is the percentage of patients went to the appointment ?

Q4: Does the medical insurance affect the appearance of the patient for the appointment ?

Q5: Does the patient's age affect their appearance for the appointment, and what is the average age of the patients that didn't go to the appointmenmt?

Q6: Does any disease like diabetes may affect patient's appearance for the appointmemnt ?

Q7: Does The Location of the hospital affect the patient's showing up?

Q8: Which category has the most absence rate and which is most attendance?

Q9: What is the relation between difference days and show status?**

Conclusions¶

From data wrangling part we found out that we have 2 cloumns that wouldn't be necessary to be involved in the analysis. by checking the dytpes we found out that schedueled day and appointment day are objects, so we needed to convert them to datetime.

After some wrangling we found that we have duplicates we did remove them from the dataset, and no NaN values found

Then we started some cleaning by dropping (ID pateint, Appointment ID), then converted all headers to lower case and add some under_scores to some of them.

No show column was represnted if yes means,that patient didn't go to the appointment, and if no means that the patient did go to the appointment, so we changed the column meaning itself to be show status if yes means done if no means absent

We found a minus value in age column we did remove it

After that we created a new column called difference which is the difference between scheduled and appointment dates

Creating a plot to show the relation between days difference and show status

We did groupby some cloumns together, we found out:

  1. There is no relation between alcohol and show_status
  2. 80% of patients are committed to the appointment Q3
  3. Patients who didn't go to the appointments being sent SMS of the appointments more than patients who did go to the appointment. Q1
  4. Female patients are more prone to miss the appoinment than males regarldless their age. Q2
  5. Scholraship or (insurance) doesn't show a big effect on people who received scholraship to show up for the appointment Q4
  6. elder patients are more committed to show up for the appointment Q5
  7. Diseased patients like with diabetes are more commited to the hospital's appointment Q6
  8. Two hospital locations have the highest rate of patient's absence (JORDIM CAMBURI) and (MARIA ORTIZ) Q7
  9. Very old patients who has more than 60 years old are more commited to the appointment time.However, Teens has the most rate of absence. Q8
